elements.name: User should be able to delete planet by clicking the delete button next to a planet, along with its associated moons

steps.name: the user is properly logged in on the home page
the user clicks the delete button next to a planet
confirm the deletion by clicking ok in the pop up window
the planet should be deleted from the table
the moons owned by that planet should be removed

elements.name: User should be able to delete moon by clicking the delete button next to a moon

steps.name: the user is properly logged in on the home page
the user clicks the delete button next to a moon
confirm the deletion by clicking ok in the pop up window
the moon should be deleted from the table

elements.name: user cannot see homepage before logging in

steps.name: the user is not logged in
the user tries to directly access the home page
the user should be denied access

elements.name: valid credentials should pass

steps.name: the user is properly logged in on the home page
the planets and moons they added should be visible
a greeting message should be present for the user

elements.name: New User(User2) logs in after User1, the planetarium table should be empty

steps.name: the user is properly logged in on the home page
the user logs out
the user should be redirected to the Login page
the user clicks the register link
provides new credentials for a second user
the user should be redirected to the Login page
the second user provides their credentials
the user clicks login
the user should be redirected to the Home page
the table should be empty
the user is properly logged in on the home page
user clicks moon creation input

elements.name: provided valid moon name, owner planet and jpg image type, new moon should be added

the user provides valid owner planet
the user decides to upload an image
the user provides a jpg filetype
